
export const monkey = {
    introduction: `Merry Monkey, you're a delightful person who never misses an opportunity and who, despite an undeniable inclination towards cunning and trickery, rarely disobeys rules. Is this contradictory? Yes, indeed, and more so. Monkeys are astute and enjoy being involved in everything. You grasp concepts long before the punchline, but you never laugh until you are truly ready. You are a meticulous plotter and planner. When faced with a seemingly impenetrable haze of human complexity, you, with your nimble spirit, will always discover the means to restore order. You are an invaluable assistant, employee, and helper. You would make an excellent vice-president. Titles and positions hold no significance for you, as you instinctively recognize that, no matter how high up you are seated, you will still merely be sitting on your posterior. Without drawing attention, you manage to skillfully orchestrate affairs from behind the scenes. You refuse to age. If you possess the financial means, you will be among the first to undergo a facelift, nose job, hair transplant, or all three!

In selecting a partner, treat yourself to a magnificent Dragon, a driven Rat, or even an impulsive Tiger, who will keep your problem-solving talents actively engaged. The initial and final periods of your life will unfold smoothly. Around the age of thirty-seven or thirty-eight, you may experience a sudden loss of confidence stemming from a significant mid-life romantic crisis. This period of despondency will pass after the age of forty-five.

My advice? Being cleverer than others is not sufficient. Knowing precisely when to take a chance and when to refrain is the secret to winning at the games you so enjoy. Refine your sense of timing through careful, patient observation. You will live longer and better on less if you learn to conserve your valuable energy (and your money) for high-stakes opportunities.`,
    elements: {
        Wood: `A fundamental characteristic of the Wood Monkey's personality is its belief in the future. This individual is constantly active and involved in everything, always engaged in some endeavor. It is perpetually constructing and creating, meticulously planning and strategizing to enhance its productivity, improve its personal environment, or contribute to making the world a more pleasant place to reside.
Wood Monkeys are inherently social creatures. They respond enthusiastically to interactions with their peers and are always seeking novel methods and locations to discover new friends, form acquaintances, and broaden their social circles. The Wood Monkey is a creative participant in social gatherings. It is the smiling individual who effortlessly navigates through any chattering crowd, meeting and greeting people with a cheerful "Hi" and "How do you do?" as if gracefully swinging from tree to tree in a lively jungle. When it comes to interacting on a purely sociable, superficial level, the Wood Monkey is unequivocally exceptional.
The less positive aspect of the Wood Monkey's high degree of affability is that it often struggles (or fails) to maintain long-term, meaningful friendships. Somehow, the good-natured charm that this Monkey exudes in public simply doesn't possess enough depth to sustain and strengthen lasting relationships. It suffers from a profound lack of genuine intimacy, often pondering why people find it so captivating and alluring, yet cease to be its friend after only a brief acquaintance. It is convinced that its intentions are honorable. It strives to be helpful and generous. Where, then, does the Wood Monkey go wrong?
Perhaps it doesn't make enough effort to truly get to know its friends and companions. Although it intends to be charitable and genuinely cares about the welfare of others, the Wood Monkey cannot remain still for long. It aims to be useful in the world and genuinely desires to cultivate many friendships, but it doesn't take the time to sit down and truly engage with friends, to listen to their troubles. It dislikes waiting for things to develop naturally, always believing it knows best. It is restless and talks excessively. It is perpetually in a hurry and shows little compassion for individuals it considers weak. If devoted friendship is what it seeks, the communicative Wood Monkey is missing the crucial point. Either it fails to truly absorb what it hears, or it simply doesn't listen in the first place.
The Wood Monkey becomes frustrated when it realizes that others cannot always keep up with its fast-paced lifestyle. It is compulsively impulsive and is sharply critical of slow-moving, single-minded individuals and those who prefer to approach life at a relaxed pace. Although it values efficiency, it fails to recognize that a slower, methodical approach can be just as effective as rapid action.
This particular type of Monkey is a social climber, a name-dropper. It feels secure when surrounded by influential people who offer both social standing and resources. It is inclined to seek romantic partners among those it perceives as socially superior, as it fears being excluded if it is not accepted by equals or superiors. This gregarious individual requires ample external reassurance that it will be included, loved, and, most importantly, permitted to remain within its peer group for an extended period.
A commendable quality that consistently saves the day for this impulsive creature is its good nature. This resilient individual knows how to be the subject of jokes and still maintain a cheerful demeanor. It gets teased because of its obvious desire to be liked, but it possesses a strong grasp of its own self-image. It is difficult to wound the ego of this amiable person.
Wood Monkeys are driven achievers. They need and desire to advance. They envision themselves ending up far beyond where they began in life. To accomplish their ambitious goals, Wood Monkeys constantly analyze the competition for weaknesses and strategize to win in the most socially acceptable manner.
For the Wood Monkey to truly succeed, it must learn to relax, to slow down, and, most importantly, to delve deeper into friendships and embrace intimate human connection. Unless it can learn to listen attentively to the needs of others, all the superficial chatter and back-slapping in the world will not lead it to its desired destination. If it applies itself, the Wood Monkey can learn to share and exchange its deepest thoughts and ideals, rather than merely presenting them, like a bundle of ripe bananas, to everyone it encounters and then continuing on its cheerful but solitary path.`,
        Fire: `Fire Monkeys enjoy being dominant in all their undertakings. Unlike most Monkeys, these types remain very much focused on their personal goals, creating and shaping their enterprises as they progress. Fire Monkeys are driven and ambitious. They desire results and are not afraid to seek the means to achieve them. The Fire Monkey is a self-starter whose enormous energy, although sometimes inconsistent and uneven, propels him speedily through life.
As the Fire Monkey's mind is fertile—his imagination is teeming with projects and innovative plans—he is doubly blessed. His capacity for hard work, coupled with his gift for invention, should make him a professional wizard. This Monkey will initiate trends, establish a new fashion in clothing or food, invent a novel literary style, or launch a new film project. But even with his myriad talents and dynamic personality, if he isn'tcareful, he may exhaust himself before he is halfway to his goal.
Although Fire Monkeys possess all the vigor, drive, and authority necessary for high achievement, they also crave the baser thrills of "having a good time." Over-indulgence in gambling, late nights in clubs, and engaging in frivolous activities may deplete their strength; indeed, these pursuits may take precedence over their initial lofty ambitions. Though not inherently excessive, Fire Monkeys are driven by the promise of excitement. They also have a dangerous taste for perversion. Some accuse them of being outright corrupt. If not curbed, Fire Monkeys can easily overload their systems and ruin their lives.
Fire Monkeys are deeply passionate, driven individuals. They respond to every experience with lightning speed and emotion. They bravely contend with the complexities of accomplishing tasks and seem almost inspired by setbacks—stimulated by adversity. To the agile-minded Fire Monkey, nothing is impossible. He seeks out and discovers solutions to the most challenging problems. He's cunning and resilient, flexible and sharp. The Fire Monkey is always willing to take a chance or embrace a new opportunity.
Though adaptable in spirit and free-wheeling, Fire Monkeys enjoy controlling others. You will often find them drawn to or living with partners of lesser willpower who need them for support or who look to them for emotional stability. Fire Monkeys may choose their lovers because of their own need to dominate someone less forceful. Yet the tables often turn on this would-be dominator, and, through an odd system of emotional manipulation and unavoidable entanglement, the Fire Monkey dominator becomes the one controlled by the mate he imagined was the weakling.
Fire Monkeys are born cynics, too. In youth, they possess a disarming air of candor, but as they mature, they grow wiser, less credulous, and sometimes even embittered. They have difficulty trusting anyone, especially their colleagues and associates. Gradually, they lose their respect for morality and begin to wear a jaundiced, knowing smile. Raw ambition provides little comfort against disappointment, but once he has lost his youthful charm and earnest beliefs, ambition is frequently all this Monkey has left.
The Fire Monkey doesn't take kindly to being made to look foolish. He is jealous in both his romantic and professional lives. He is competitive and can be vindictive, even vengeful. Speculation is his favorite game. He may take on many partners, form corporations, or assemble groups for projects, but no matter how equitable the terms of any agreement, the Fire Monkey will always insist on remaining the boss.
This Monkey is by far the most power-hungry of all Monkeys, yet he may not always be the most visible. Much of his true essence remains hidden or operates behind the scenes. Outwardly, the Fire Monkey is scornful of naive dreams and loudly dismisses ideals as trite, childish, and insipid. But the resilient Fire Monkey also yearns for a better world and would go to even greater lengths than all other Monkeys if only he believed that his wonderful dream could come true.`,
        Earth: `This Monkey is calmer, more sentimental, and a deeper thinker than most. Altruism is well developed in its character, and it is notably less carefree than its counterparts. It genuinely ponders both the past and future of humankind and attempts to comprehend the shape of things to come. Earth Monkeys love all types of people and can embrace the problems of others as if they were their own.
The Earth element bestows upon the Monkey solid natural wisdom and insight. Because it is so perceptive, it is painfully aware of certain harsh truths about life from an early age. It may speak out in family or school situations, surprising adults with unnaturally astute comments. Although silence is not its strong suit, study is. It will be capable of reaching lofty social positions through education. In China, the Earth Monkey is known as the teacher Monkey. Not only is it learned, but it is also able to impart knowledge and demonstrate devotion in the pursuit of a professorial career. Its students will be faithful admirers. They will adore its cheerful manner and are instructed and amused by the Earth Monkey's imaginative presentation of inherently difficult or dull material.
This Monkey's best attribute lies in its ability to interact with its peers: people like it immediately. It is affable and jolly, optimistic and inspirational. It's bright and witty, and so smart and intuitive that it seems to possess foresight. Even better, the Earth Monkey knows how to make us laugh. It won't waste time on gloomy reruns of its difficult childhood or tedious school exploits. It is fun, spontaneous, and full of life. It is strong without being overpowering, and yet it remains a serious, even profound, thinker.
The biggest flaw in the Earth Monkey's character is its desire for perfection. This sociable and pleasant individual seems so easy-going and fun-loving that we sometimes wonder if it can truly be taken seriously—but this Monkey is worse than serious—it's nit-picking—obsessed with perfection. It longs for a home that operates flawlessly, a family to be nothing but proud of, a designated place for everything, and everything in its place.
However, the family life of the average Earth Monkey is never a paradise. Its need for order in the inherently disorderly atmosphere of home and children leads to problems for it and its poor, subjugated offspring. Either the children and spouse become terrorized by all the obsessive fussing, or as time goes by, the meticulous Earth Monkey parent becomes a subject of family ridicule and has to seek refuge in the basement or is forced out of the nest.
This Monkey is fatally attracted to the opposite sex. An imaginative lover, it cannot resist the urge to engage in romantic play. It adores the intrigue, the chase, the seduction. Extramarital affairs are common in the life of this highly sensual Monkey. Usually, fear of scandal (the specter of imperfection again) prevents it from confessing its indiscretions to a passing newspaper reporter. It hates to acknowledge its own mistakes, yet is quick to point out those of its family. Living intimately with the Earth Monkey is not for amateurs: it requires more than patience—even a spirit of masochistic self-sacrifice. Yet this Monkey is kind and can be reached through a large, tender window of guilt. If reminded of how difficult it is, the Earth Monkey will rally. Beneath its challenging, superficial nature, it is devoted to those it loves and can always be counted on to provide and maintain order.
The Earth Monkey is blessed with good health and a sturdy constitution. It will live to a ripe old age. With its innate talents for study and concentration, it could work in scientific research, law enforcement, or history. Because of its ability to work independently, it can pursue a career in the arts as an independent filmmaker, a literary scholar, a painter, or sculptor.
If an Earth Monkey could improve one aspect of its character, it should definitely be its perfection-seeking tendency. It could and should partake of some of life's simple pleasures. Earth Monkeys need to relax their overly traditional side, break down personal barriers that prevent them from enjoying a relaxed lifestyle, and rid themselves of the need to show off their brilliant achievements in public. Developing the spiritual side of this neurotically driven perfectionist is a sure way to loosen those inhibitions for something more profound than clandestine extracurricular sex.`,
        Metal: `The intellectual aspect of this Monkey helps it to be a creative, self-made individual. It typically prefers to forge its own path alone, working contentedly at a profession that leads it into elevated realms.
This independent person will encounter numerous obstacles on the journey to discovering its unique niche. However, it will certainly find it—or perish trying! This is the fighting Monkey. When uncertain, it confronts issues, battles inner demons, and fiercely attacks adversaries. It often triumphs through persuasion, reason, and logic. But, if the situation demands it, it is unafraid to engage in physical confrontation and decisively defeat its opponent. The Metal Monkey's strength is not like the stormy, fiery bravado of a Dragon, nor can it match the Ox or Rooster for perseverance and endurance. The Metal Monkey appears resilient and aggressive. It simply annihilates challengers through intellectual might and a twist of spirit. Then it leaves the defeated behind and moves forward, as spirited as ever, to challenge the next contender. It's tough—but in a commendable way.
The Metal Monkey's personal life is never a romantic novel. It is determined to achieve a significant position in its career, make its mark on society, and push its creative ideas through established systems, leaving little time for family or emotional space. As a major innovator, it must possess unconventional ideas. It is neither obedient to norms nor overtly revolutionary, but it requires the thrill of achievement, advancement, and status. It desires to be where the action is, and if its associates do not understand, then that is their problem.
It is, of course, possible for this individual to marry and maintain a semblance of family life. Metal Monkeys are usually financially secure and make good providers, but they may not be inclined to spend much time at home. This person needs an independent, loving, and patient mate, unafraid to take sole responsibility for the home, family, and marriage.
Metal Monkeys possess sociable, gregarious personalities. They converse extensively and (although they are Monkeys) are often capable of learning foreign languages. They enjoy travel and are quite likely to move abroad early in adulthood, relocating to start anew in a different place to satisfy their desire for self-sovereignty. The Metal Monkey dislikes criticism, does not wish to be compared to siblings and/or cousins, and deplores the existence of relatives who insist on burdening it with unsolicited advice. The Metal Monkey desires to be distinct, officially unattached—an individual. It forges its own path and refuses to credit its frequent successes and financial gains to anyone else.
The Metal Monkey is intelligent. It is argumentative, yet possesses a charming, winning demeanor. The close relative who lives with this captivating person knows just how irritable and particular it can be, and resents all the extra affection and praise that the Metal Monkey receives from its numerous admirers. For the Metal Monkey, family situations are often tense and fraught with animosity. Metal Monkeys are the kind of people who try to seize the family home from sisters and brothers to convert it into an elderly care facility which, naturally, bears the Metal Monkey's illustrious name.
The Metal Monkey can be prone to melancholy. If this person (who would perform amateur open-heart surgery on friend or foe to achieve their goals) does not succeed, they may succumb to despair. All that pushing, shoving, and strategizing is so exhausting, and the stakes are so all-or-nothing, that the fatigued Metal Monkey sometimes cannot muster the energy to begin all over again. Its flaw lies in its inflated self-image—its pride. It can handle setbacks as long as it emerges victorious. Too many losses, and it retreats, dejected and hopeless. One sometimes wonders how many struggling individuals are Metal Monkeys who simply gave up.
When and if despair sets in, the Metal Monkey may attribute its failures to its upbringing, its family, friends, or associates who were jealous and tried to undermine it. This "poor me" attitude is characteristic of an undeveloped personality that cannot accept its own shortcomings, will not assume responsibility for communication breakdowns, and can only perceive itself as a victim. Truly, this attitude leads to a dead end.
The remedy for despondency in Metal Monkeys is structured group therapy. Although I don't often recommend it, I view the Metal Monkey as so oblivious to its own errors and so unwilling from an early age to consult with or take advice from elders or peers that it cannot help but benefit from a group experience. Metal Monkeys do not realize that they cannot always be right. They need to learn early on to accept feedback from those around them.
This Monkey makes an excellent salesman or TV talk-show host, newscaster, or disc jockey. It is so articulate and quick-witted that it could sell fur coats to bears. Whatever verbal challenge arises, it meets it with composure and a smooth-talking manner. It makes strangers feel comfortable. It exudes confidence and competence even when it has no idea what it's doing.
Finally, expect nothing but the best from the brilliant side of this person. Leonardo da Vinci was a Metal Monkey, as is Pope John Paul. These Monkeys are profoundly individualistic. This signifies achievement and versatility. Metal Monkeys can learn how to do almost anything.
However, if Metal Monkeys experience too many failures, their mental and physical health will deteriorate. They are born with more pride than resilience. The fracturing of this fragile surface can destroy their cheerful demeanor, and they may quickly begin to crumble into oblivion.`,
        Water: `A sublime blend of cooperation and genius, the Water Monkey is truly exceptional! Inquire around; everyone agrees. It is one of the world's most spirited individuals.
Although Water Monkeys can always be relied upon to defend their own interests, they are generous individuals, willing to lend a hand or share whatever abundance they possess. Water Monkeys are never careless friends who casually walk through your living room, grab a piece of fruit, and quickly depart without leaving more than a faint scent of patchouli. They take friendship and love seriously. Not that they become overly effusive about their affection, but from the moment they decide to welcome a friend into their circle, their devotion is genuine, their willingness to assist when someone needs help is constant, and their loyalty is unwavering.
Water Monkeys are clever and witty without being cynical. There is a sweetness to their affability, and they are always seeking to help others realize their dreams. They possess an innate ability to care deeply without being overly sentimental. They do not mind relinquishing the spotlight in favor of someone they admire, and except for a basic need to maintain a modicum of security, they are extravagantly generous with everything from hospitality to money, praise, and affection.
The Water Monkey possesses an elfin or lively quality. A whimsical energy permeates everything it does. It is constantly radiating vibes of ironic cheerfulness, which blends perfectly with its natural tenderness towards others. Consider the teasing cartoons of Sempé, the lyrical films of Milos Forman, or the biting yet humane works of François Truffaut. There's something both socially commendable and subtly sarcastic about the way Water Monkeys view life. They are critical and caring simultaneously. They don't mind pointing out the flaws of friends and relatives, but they wouldn't hurt them for anything, because they care so intensely about their happiness.
Water Monkeys do not always fare as well as their friends. They tend to be unnecessarily neurotic. They are easily overcome by worry and become bewildered when minor things go wrong—they may grow anxious when the hall porter forgets to say good morning. Perhaps the porter is having a bad day and forgot to greet him—but it will trouble the Water Monkey, who may not be able to let himself, or you, forget it for weeks. The insignificant incident is exaggerated out of all proportion, and the Water Monkey suffers. It is always he who apologizes and makes amends.
Water Monkeys are ingenious problem-hunters—and solvers. They do not want to hear the word "impossible." For a Water Monkey, navigating a dense thicket of thorns means devising a way around it—and the Water Monkey makes an excellent mediator, troubleshooter, or organizer. It is a great motivator—it can spend its life urging, scolding, monitoring, identifying, and rectifying flaws, and be contentedly fulfilled with that secondary role.
The Water Monkey is never a prima donna or an egomaniac. The innovative talents of this warm, loving person would not suit continuous talk show appearances. The Water Monkey's ego is contained within the clever mind of a generous soul. Even Elizabeth Taylor, with her astonishing beauty, has never become a captivating siren like Zsa Zsa Gabor or a delightfully simpering Marilyn Monroe. She's always married to some man with a giant ego whom she's trying to cure of alcoholism (and perhaps getting caught up herself) or helping to combat prejudice about AIDS. Liz Taylor is a failure as a prima donna because she simply wasn't born selfish enough.
Gloom and depression can cause the Water Monkey's buoyant spirit to plummet. If its minor neuroses or others’ demands close in on it, and it's made to feel guilty, its high spirits may crash. The idea of being wrong unnerves it, and as it blames itself for much that goes wrong anyway, it is ill-equipped to defend itself against accusations. Water Monkeys are easy targets for manipulative individuals who ruthlessly exploit their sympathies.
There is something of the cheerful meddler in the Water Monkey. Sometimes it becomes intrusive. Water Monkeys enjoy gossip, which contributes to their reputation as sociable companions and excellent friends. But occasionally, they reveal someone else's secrets when they might be better off choosing to "speak no evil."
Water Monkeys are intensely sensual. They adore engaging in the act of love. They revel in all the imaginative ways to play the oldest human game. Unfortunately, they are rarely cool-headed in their choice of lovers and cannot resist becoming involved with complex and difficult individuals. Perhaps it is natural for the problem-solver to take on problematic people. Water Monkeys consistently find unyielding, challenging partners with irritable tempers and precarious emotional foundations. Individuals whom you or I might happily remove from our lives, Water Monkeys adopt as cherished companions. They are irresistibly drawn to experiencing perplexing scenarios in the hope that they will play a key role in untangling the most stubborn knots.`,
    },
    compatibilities: {
        "Rat": "If all else fails, these two can go on the road as a comedy duo. Humor, games, parties, and friends! What fun you’ll have! How lucky you are to have been brought together! Shared, your lives will be a never-ending roller-coaster ride. The amusing Monkey, incessantly grimacing from the top of the jungle gym, has the Rat in perpetual stitches. Amid guffaws, the Rat suggests funnier, more clever antics, fueling the witty Monkey with ever more hysterical moves. It’s a matrimonial picnic. The sometimes-repressed Rat will become a tiresome chatterbox alongside a mellow Monkey. But the Monkey never tires of the clever Rat. For him, it’s like owning a walking radio show. Both so personable, they will always be dining out or entertaining at home. They have a multitude of friends and spend little time alone. As neither is afraid of hard work, money comes easily to them. The Monkey sometimes uses characteristically diverse interests to justify a desire for sexual promiscuity. Should Monkey betray the ever-devoted Rat, the relationship will become strained. But terminal dissension is rare. Mostly, this gleeful couple lives in an amusement park of joy.",
        "Ox": "If the Ox can relinquish stubborn conformism and trust his beloved Monkey, the Monkey can greatly improve the quality of an Ox’s life. In return for the Monkey’s gift of freedom, the Ox will lend security to his Monkey mate. Much to everyone’s surprise, the Ox, usually incensed by any disturbance of routine, is fascinated by the tricky Monkey. Monkey, in turn, tries harder to amuse and enchant his faithful mate. Both are basically practical and project-oriented. Moreover, Monkeys can teach Oxen to step outside themselves, be willingly kind to others, to help out the less fortunate. Charity gives the Ox a special thrill. He is grateful to the Monkey for opening his eyes to the needs of the poor. Under the covers, expect the imaginative Monkey to spice up the Ox’s humdrum technique. With the Monkey’s agile tutelage the Ox can expect to learn much more than a few dancing techniques. He may even learn how to fly!",
        "Tiger": "These two make eager lovers. Initially, they will leap frequently on each other’s bones, accomplishing astonishing feats of extreme passion, but in the long run, the ardor may die a natural death, because Tigers hate to be clung to—and innately neurotic Monkeys don’t know how not to cling. The strong intellectual tug between Tigers and Monkeys frequently keeps them together, anyway. The Tiger admires the Monkey’s keen eye for strategy and the Monkey enjoys and applauds the Tiger’s feisty wit and temerity. Monkey gives Tiger plenty of presents and kudos. Tiger gives Monkey spunk and encouragement. These two have an easy common viewpoint and, even if they cannot keep the love flame burning, will go far together as lifelong pals. Except… the Chinese say that the Tiger should beware. Traditionally, the Monkey is Tiger’s natural enemy. I don’t advise marriage.",
        "Rabbit": "These two people are intellectually well matched. They both enjoy being in cultural venues, seeking out new exhibitions or museums and learning about subjects of particular interest to one or both of them. The meeting of two like minds can be the basis of a lifetime of wedded harmony. Emotionally, however, there will be snags. The Cat hates change and does not enjoy surprises. Discretion, for the Cat, is nine-tenths of the law. Monkeys live for change, enjoy leaping about from place to place and adore being in the limelight, amusing cronies and carrying on high in public. Moreover, the Cat takes him- or herself very seriously. Not too many jokes allowed. Monkeys make fun of everything (including their mates) and think of the world as a giant silliness. The success and longevity of this relationship depends on the degree of passion the couple can extract from their intensely cerebral friendship. Neither lends much belief to the idea of syrupy romance, keeping their respective cynical distances from all “sentimental” notions. They may require a push from an outside source (e.g. Dicey love triangle, savvy therapist, good friend etc) to accept to surrender to the natural human impulse to love and be loved—no matter what!",
        "Dragon": "Despite the obvious differences in their characters, these two have a lot going for them. The Dragon is bombastic and needs to be adored, yet reveres the Monkey’s keen intelligence and ability to see around corners. Monkeys love spectacle and invariably enjoy the show Dragons put on. Dragons get themselves embroiled in world problems. Monkeys are born solvers of problems—big and little. There is plenty of room for personal evolution in this couple. Impressed by the efficiency of the Monkey’s exceptional mind, the Dragon (atypically) will become almost dependent, let up on the accelerator from time to time and even take an occasional back seat to Monkey’s brilliance. Monkeys enjoy being appreciated for their skillful talents, are not particularly interested in the number one position, and let a Dragon bask in the footlights. As a result of this clever balance, the Dragon/Monkey match becomes a strong bond, built on compromise and mutual respect. Sex, however, may not be the strongest element that binds these two. The Monkey’s normally healthy appetite seems moderate by comparison to the Dragon’s voracious and conspicuous need for consumption of his or her mate’s intimate favors.",
        "Snake": "Auspicious beginnings encourage these characters to join forces and operate as a team. The versatile Monkey finds wisdom and consideration in the Snake’s personality. The Snake enjoys the Monkey’s charm and peppy energy. They are truly a complementary pair. After a time, however, they will see that all they have in common is a taste for helping others, a charitable bent which binds them ever so loosely together. Snake, of course, always takes off on extramarital adventures. Monkey? Well, Monkey couldn’t care less: if affairs turn up, so much the better. If not, he can take them or leave them alone. Snakes like elegance and want their lives carefully accessorized. Monkeys are bored by the very idea of accessorizing anything, and dress down rather than dressing up. Monkeys are spontaneous. Snakes ponderous. Snake is romantic, Monkey logical. Snake is sophisticated, Monkey Bohemian and carefree. Monkeys love to converse, but dialogue becomes difficult because Snakes find it hard to divulge their inner feelings. Breakdown in communications might be the death of this relationship. Their sex life usually compensates for much of the strife between them. Although sex is not always the Monkey’s strongest suit, Snakes succeed in turning them on in a big way. The complicity of elaborate sex games may ensure a basis for this pair to consolidate their union—despite their essential differences.",
        "Horse": "A mutual desire to stay abreast of events, mingle in society and be part of what’s happening in the outside world will constitute the initial attraction between these two. Monkeys are so versatile, imaginative and amusing that Horses have trouble resisting their charms. Monkeys feel that serious Horses need cheering up and are inspired to make them laugh. Monkeys also appreciate the Horse’s strict sense of duty and ability to endure hard work. They love to join forces and solve problems together. Communication may not be their strongest suit. Monkeys are inveterate neurotics who cherish their unhealthy behavior patterns and although they chatter, they don’t open up easily. Horses are guarded and conservative about speaking up on their own behalf. Much tension may build. They should agree (before reaching the ulcer stage) to see a therapist regularly. Otherwise, unexpressed emotions will cause the death of their union. A brilliant sex life is in store for the Monkey/Horse couple. They are mutually energetic and fanciful about romance. Horse may want more sex than does Monkey, but Monkey’s fertile imagination will more than compensate for lack of appetite. As long as these two don’t sit around complacently, patting each other on the back about how well their couple “works”, they can create a lasting bond.",
        "Goat": "A mutual lightheartedness will draw these two creatures into a joyous relationship. The Monkey’s energy alone can carry the couple and, as the Monkey is very generous, he or she will not mind being the sole provider. If Monkey is doing well, their whole existence can consist of fun and games. The sex will be less than wonderful, though, because Monkey isn’t the same sort of sensitive lover as the Goat. Goats need constant caresses, are romantic and sentimental, while Monkeys are practical lovers whose lovemaking resembles a healthful gymnastic more than a swooning match. The Goat’s moral dependence may become irritating to the Monkey, who longs to move about freely without undue constraint. Having to stay at home, coaxing a grumpy Goat out of pessimistic moods and rousing him from inertia may be more than the independent Monkey can bear. If this couple has a family, it may help to hold them together. Goat can stay securely at home while Monkey wanders free. It’s a sound combination, providing the Monkey can eventually support Goat in leisurely style.",
        "Monkey": "These two make great companions. They love in a hands-off fashion. Neither interferes with the other’s progress merely looking for ego-strokes. Two Monkeys usually create a project-oriented family atmosphere wherein each member of the group has individual responsibilities and householding belongs to everyone. Cooking and washing up, shopping and even ironing may be shared equally. The male Monkey is never too proud to do laundry. And Ms. Monkey doesn’t mind changing the oil in the car. Monkeys are race, creed and color blind. Sexually slanted competition doesn’t exist between these two. Problems (and there aren’t many that two Monkeys can’t solve better than one) will arise in the financial arena. Neither Monkey likes doing accounts, writing checks or letters protesting gas and electricity bills. As a couple, they may fall behind and ruin their reputation. As both are work and people-oriented, this couple will need to hire a bookkeeper to hold their finances together. Sex is not often the foremost consideration between two Monkeys. They both enjoy it and even prefer having sex with each other. But they are not overly preoccupied by the intensity or endurance of their sexual lives. If and when it happens, they are excited and happy. Without it, neither curls up and dies. Promiscuity might be a dot on the horizon, but dalliances are of no consequence, as Monkeys make committed couples who believe in personal freedom.",
        "Rooster": "Not much is going on sexually between these two characters. Roosters are possessive and anxious about their position in relationships. Their instinct is to anchor their prey. Monkeys need miles of rope to feel good about themselves. They have to roam amid people, jabber with others and find solutions to ever more important problems. Roosters are conservative thinkers. Monkeys are all for liberation, gentler laws and personal liberty. This couple may be constantly at odds over policy. Decisions become difficult. Tensions rise and Rooster suffers—because Rooster makes the untenable scenes that send the Monkey packing. Roosters must accept Monkey’s devil-may-care side to enjoy the benefit of his or her humor. It’s up to the Rooster to be more flexible. And that is a tall order. So these two are not exactly Romeo and Juliet. Monkey is interested in sex, but he’s also fascinated by life’s other aspects—above all its practicalities. Rooster is also practical and appreciates Monkey’s delight in solving concrete issues. But Rooster needs softening, romancing, loving and cuddling to appreciate the joys of sex. Now it’s Monkey’s turn to adapt, to become more languorous and spend time petting and nuzzling. Or Rooster (God forbid!) might begin scratching around in another barnyard for sexual understanding.",
        "Dog": "The Dog is a blazing idealist. The Monkey lives for the opportune moment. They may well meet up and fall in love when engaged in a social struggle together. Each possesses qualities lacking in the other. Although this might make them seem perfectly matched, it takes more than dovetailing qualities to make two such impervious individualists communicate. Each is so accustomed to living on his own wavelength that they have real trouble shifting gears to make themselves understood to someone on another plane. The remedy is talk. These two nervous souls must sit and yammer for hours, days and months before they reach comprehension. The Dog will have to give up blurting nasty remarks and the Monkey must accept being tethered for at least part of the time. Although they can be guilty of it, Dogs don’t take kindly to philandering. But Monkeys like sexual freedom. Monkey seems carefree and Dog laughably frustrated. Being of basic good intention, if they wish to stay together, this pair can work out a harmonious sex life together. This relationship’s harmony is possible but will not be won without effort. Unless the union is inevitable, I advise imagining it can work forever.",
        "Pig": "Piggy! The Pig must treat this relationship with less blind indulgence for the opposite party. Monkeys can be ruthless when necessary. The Pig’s naïveté is no help when it comes to dealing with a beloved, yet sometimes unscrupulous, Monkey. Unlike the Snake, whose intentions in the Pig’s regard are plainly lethal, the Monkey means no harm. Pigs’ and Monkeys’ tender hearts are mightily compatible—but their thinking processes are worlds apart. The Pig must adapt to the Monkey’s ways or the couple is doomed. As Pigs are very malleable, adaptation is not an unreasonable demand. But Piggy must be careful not to lose his or her purest ideals in Monkey’s constantly expanding bag of tricks. Pigs live by intuition. Monkeys cleave to logic. If they can teach their mutual talents to cooperate, it will assist their union’s progress. If not, there will be major rows. An angry Monkey is a hopping mad mini-volcano who forgets about it two minutes after the eruption. A mad Pig is fearsome, relentless, dangerous and vengeful. Monkey should accept and enjoy Pig’s smothering and homely charms. And Pig should try to see how innocently the Monkey needs room to wander and squander. If these concessions are made, they can have a lovely, long-lasting life复工",
    },
    futures: {
        "2025": { "year": "Snake", "element": "Yin Wood", "prediction": `This period is not precisely a time of ideal comfort for Monkeys; Snake years will require you to perform some intricate adaptive maneuvers. The Snake is a composed and collected individual, characterized by a no-nonsense and philosophical demeanor, and Snakes do not require or desire constant entertainment. Of course, they appreciate a high-quality professional show or concert, where they can dress appropriately in their finest attire and enjoy the play or music at a suitable, socially acceptable pace. However, Monkeys riding around on unicycles or playing trumpets in their bathrooms while dressed as scarecrows or nuns? That is met with very little enthusiasm, and only in extremely small, carefully measured doses. Fundamentally, the Snake disapproves of the Monkey’s eccentric approach. Therefore, in this year governed by the sober Snake, you should temper your slapstick humor. Refine your comedic routines so they convey a more serious tone, and reduce your physical comedy. If you manage to quiet yourself down, you will discover the company of the wise Snake to be extremely beneficial. Listen to the Snake’s advice. Make the necessary adjustments and changes to adapt to the prevailing mood of this year, and you will be free to advance swiftly in all your endeavors. Since you enjoy giving presents as readily as others change their socks, feel free to lavish gifts! Be generous with your giving this year—and particularly choose beautiful accessories; handbags, jewelry, scarves, gloves, hats, ties, and cufflinks of the finest quality will be greatly appreciated by the recipients. Snakes have an intense fondness for accessories.` },
        "2026": { "year": "Horse", "element": "Yang Fire", "prediction": `The Monkey’s fundamental problem-solving nature holds strong appeal for the practical Horse. This year, the Horse will not obstruct the Monkey’s progress. On the contrary, Monkeys will be encouraged to utilize their diverse skills and manage affairs in their own clever way. Do not interfere. Do not attempt to take control. When the situation begins to falter and threaten to derail, simply close your eyes and hum a cheerful tune. Horses do not appreciate being helped, confined, restricted, or criticized. This, of course, is a significant challenge for Monkey individuals, who can discern the intricacies of almost any situation and always wish to offer assistance in a crisis. Horses frequently find themselves in difficult predicaments. My advice to Monkeys? Stay out of it. Unless the Horse year begins to become unstable and threaten to bring down your own household, absolutely refrain from offering any advice or inserting yourself into complex situations. (If you are an in-law, this advice is particularly directed at you.) Allow this year to resolve its own difficulties. Attend all the parties you are invited to. Entertain enthusiastically. But do not attempt to steal the spotlight or try to take over where others have already established themselves (this applies to deals, relationships, business projects, inventions, etc.). Your role this year is to keep pace with the swift and winding Horse year’s hectic rhythm and avoid losing your composure.` },
        "2027": { "year": "Goat", "element": "Yin Fire", "prediction": `Your inherent generosity must be restrained during the Goat year. You tend to see someone in need, and when you can, you instinctively reach into your pocket or purse. It’s not that you are careless with money, but you possess an open-handed attitude regarding what you have to spare. You give many presents, and you enjoy treating your friends and family to delightful meals in charming restaurants or taking them on trips to interesting new places. The Goat year may exert just a little too much pressure on your finances. You will perceive opportunities for charitable or altruistic acts and impulsively fall headlong into their tempting demands. Hold back. Watch your pennies carefully. Goats love Monkeys and are particularly drawn to their ability to be creative in so many different areas. In this respect, you two are quite similar. However, caution is advised. Goats are perpetually seeking someone to lend them money, provide assistance, offer housing and sustenance, and well… take care of their everyday needs so that they can continue with whatever they are currently engaged in. Monkeys simply cannot afford to take on Goats. Therefore, this year, be especially cunning when some unfortunate individual asks you for a handout or a loan. Smile, claim financial hardship, and firmly say NO.` },
        "2028": { "year": "Monkey", "element": "Yang Earth", "prediction": `During your travels this year, you will encounter someone who will exert a profound influence on your career. This could be an older person who takes a particular liking to one of your brilliant ideas. Alternatively, it might be a contemporary who is willing to partner with you, either in business or in love. Pay close attention to this person’s Chinese astrological sign and compare it with your own. If the compatibility is harmonious, seriously consider pursuing a joint project or a marriage together. This is your year to shine, to preen, to assert yourself, and to dance on tables if you feel inclined. However, do remember to return to Earth occasionally, because this is also the year for you to plan the next twelve years of your life. The Chinese calendar does not use ten-year decades; instead, it employs twelve-year periods. Each year holds a particular significance for every zodiac sign. When your own year arrives, you are obligated to sit down with pen and paper (or a computer) and outline the next twelve years of your life. Where do you wish to be in 2040? What do you envision yourself doing? How might you meticulously plot the path to this objective, year by year, to ensure you are more or less certain to achieve that goal? Is this an easy task? No. But it is a necessary exercise for constructing your own life. Take charge of your destiny in this auspicious Monkey year. Do not simply sit back and allow life to dictate your path.` },
        "2029": { "year": "Rooster", "element": "Yin Earth", "prediction": `In this year, Roosters consistently take a liking to Monkeys because they recognize that Monkeys are the most amusing individuals around, and Roosters genuinely need to be entertained. Furthermore, Roosters are greatly impressed by your ability to resolve even the most intricate problems. You two are not at all similar. Roosters tend to be somber, rigid, and serious individuals. You Monkeys, by contrast, are quick-witted and agile in both body and spirit. Nevertheless, in this Rooster year, you will benefit from considerable goodwill. You can earn a significant amount of money, acquire numerous desirable items for yourself (such as cars, restaurant ranges, boats, houses, and—if you are so inclined—even an occasional winery or ranch). Best of all, in this unusually generous-to-Monkeys year, you will possess enough disposable income to lavish your loved ones (and even those you don't care for as much) with an abundance of presents. There will be days in this Rooster year when you return home laden with gifts for everyone. It will be like Father Christmas in July or Mother Christmas in September. Be vigilant for an overly cunning associate who (while you were on your shopping spree in Mendoza, Napa, or Burgundy) may have been embezzling funds. It could be your accountant, but it might also be your spouse or significant other. You will instinctively know how best to resolve this issue. Why? Because you’re a Monkey, of course!` },
        "2030": { "year": "Dog", "element": "Yang Metal", "prediction": `Dogs are inherently mistrustful and prone to sarcasm. You Monkeys are well aware of corruption and savvy about the unsavory underbelly of the world. However, you would prefer to disregard all that and simply live for the present moment and enjoy something delightful to eat. The Dog year is not disastrous for Monkey individuals, but it is certainly not an easy period either. Firstly, financial difficulties may arise. In Dog years, money tends to be scarce. Dogs do not believe in waste and prefer not to live in lavish luxury or witness displays of excessive consumption. Dogs are champions for justice and are eager to see things done correctly. They are also remarkably blunt and critical, uttering disagreeable remarks without realizing how sharp and unkind they sound. You Monkeys want no part of this cynicism and do not care to join any movements aimed at improving the lives of homeless children in Brazil; it simply isn't your inclination. So, in Dog years, you will want to reduce your spending (which you needed to do anyway) and stay informed about current events. You will undoubtedly be called upon several times to participate in rallies advocating for the future of married Gay priests or to march for the right to life of all the litters of all the dogs in the thousands of animal shelters across your country. Do not be surprised. Maintain your amusing demeanor. Do not become depressed. Work diligently and frequently change your phone number to deter the do-gooders who will crowd your driveway if you allow them.` },
        "2031": { "year": "Pig", "element": "Yin Metal", "prediction": `The pure-hearted Pig harbors little respect for you impulsive Monkeys. It's not that Pigs are joy-killers or wish to diminish your vibrancy; they don't. However, Pigs would rather luxuriate before a warm wood fire with a glass of the finest cognac, a Havana cigar, and engaging conversation than join a group of frolicking Monkeys on a noisy, smoky, and wild dance floor somewhere. Consequently, in this year, although you cannot rely on the Pig’s complete cooperation, you can depend on your own spirited nature to go out, earn money, and enjoy hobbies, sports, and other enjoyable activities. This would be an excellent year for you to join an amateur theater company or participate in some form of group therapy. You know how skilled you are at solving other people’s problems, right? Well, you are not known for being able to resolve your own. Monkeys are inherently neurotic. Somehow, you are blind to your own internal struggles and often simply stand there weeping and staring blankly at the challenges. All forms of talk therapy are recommended. You need to thoroughly discuss things to gain a comprehensive understanding of what is troubling you. If you can perceive yourself as others do, you will have made significant progress towards emotional health. The Pig is definitely on your side in this endeavor.` },
        "2032": { "year": "Rat", "element": "Yang Water", "prediction": `After navigating through a couple of challenging years, you are finally in a space where you will be understood, celebrated, and admired for an entire year. Rats and Monkeys get along exceptionally well, like a perfectly matched pair. The Rat is an emotional individual who often struggles with making decisions. Should I buy a red car or a blue car? Marry a Dragon or a Tiger? Accept that new job offer or remain in my current position? How should I structure my life now that my parents are no longer around to influence me? What should I wear to the ball? By now, we all recognize that whenever one is grappling with a dilemma, whether large or small, the solution is to seek assistance from a Monkey. Monkeys cannot resolve their own problems very quickly, but they are masters at helping others make swift, practical choices. So, in a Rat year, you Monkey individuals will find yourselves frequently called upon to offer advice, to untangle complex issues, or to calm someone whose temper has them in a state of advanced agitation. You can always figure out the most graceful way to exit a difficult situation. Since you are not driven by power and never wish to be in the forefront, you are not in competition with the authority-seeking Rat. In other words, for Monkeys in Rat years, everything is proceeding smoothly.` },
        "2033": { "year": "Ox", "element": "Yin Water", "prediction": `Your preference for novelty and untested experiences can irritate the Ox. Oxen prefer things to remain (as much as possible) exactly as they were. So, you will confidently enter the Ox year, having just completed a satisfying Rat year where you pursued your own interests, and then—bam!—you will encounter the unyielding Ox temperament. However, there's no need to worry. Oxen can utilize some of your vibrant energy, so climb aboard the Ox’s strong back and progress through this year at its unhurried pace. For Monkeys, Ox years are periods of rest. The Ox protects you from your own tendencies and may even help prevent health issues by slowing you down and prompting you to thoroughly examine certain underlying concerns you've been needing to address. How is your relationship faring? What is the status of your career? How is your overall health? This is a time for medical checkups and dental examinations. Long conversations and strolls on the beach with your loved one (or ones) should help resolve any lingering grievances. Ensure your blood pressure is within a healthy range, and make sure to join a gym or take a tai chi class. Given your often erratic eating habits, the enforced slowdown in an Ox year could cause your body to expand significantly within a matter of weeks. Walk, run, jump—but avoid remaining stagnant.` },
        "2034": { "year": "Tiger", "element": "Yang Wood", "prediction": `The Tiger consistently welcomes the presence of a Monkey in its midst, though not always continuously or for extended periods. In Chinese astrology, Monkeys and Tigers are traditionally considered adversaries. In practice, however, Tigers often befriend Monkeys, and vice versa. Nevertheless, what Tigers often do not reveal is that they frequently appreciate the company of Monkeys because Monkeys can resolve problems that Tigers cannot. Tigers enjoy Monkey humor and are somewhat entertained by their antics. But the true reason that you Monkeys will not face a difficult path this year is that the Tiger finds you useful. A business question? A travel predicament? Lost luggage? Lost love? Lost jobs? Simply "Dial-a-Monkey"—which is precisely what the Tiger year will prompt you to do. You will be called upon to advise and counsel others throughout this busy Tiger year. People may awaken you in the middle of the night just to ascertain your opinion on their church picnic for the following month. How should Tracey approach Nancy regarding the hard-boiled eggs? Who should cook the hot dogs? What types of games are safest for the children? Any kind of problem provides fodder for the Monkey’s agile mind. And people quickly realize that you can fix things for them. So you will be sought after and respected for your opinions in this Tiger year. However, you may not get married, become wealthy, or experience some grand passion this year, simply because there won’t be enough time.` },
        "2035": { "year": "Rabbit", "element": "Yin Wood", "prediction": `Monkeys are widely known for gaining social or political influence during Cat/Rabbit years. The reason for this is quite straightforward when you consider that the Cat/Rabbit desires nothing overtly public to happen to him. He prefers to remain in the background while others perform and engage in activities on stage. You, as a Monkey, do not mind performing. In fact, entertaining others is one of your favorite pastimes. So, once again, you prove useful to the ruling sign, and what’s more, you are amusing. Cat/Rabbits often devise excellent strategies for earning or investing money, but they require a Monkey—a kind of engineer—to bring these plans to the attention of those in power. They also hold a monopoly on refinement and comfortable living. You, however, care very little about where you live and are about as refined as brown rice in a health food store bin. This disparity in styles might typically cause a rift between you and the sophisticated influences of this year. But it won't. The Cat/Rabbit employs your innate audacity to represent him, to be his spokesperson, to venture into society and present his case. That much you can and will gladly do. Therefore, this year, no tension will arise that could thwart any of your own plans. Seize the opportunity to reconfigure your life. Utilize your new contacts in high places to further your career and take pleasure from the Cat/Rabbit’s luxurious lifestyle.` },
        "2036": { "year": "Dragon", "element": "Yang Fire", "prediction": `This year is perfectly suited for ambitious Monkeys who aspire to advance their careers and enhance their credentials. Dragons welcome Monkeys into their hearts, homes, businesses, and schools with a spirit of warm hospitality. Dragons love to laugh and enjoy a hearty chuckle over something amusing or unusual. Monkeys can conjure up jokes and stunts in an instant and perform pratfalls and eccentric visual gags without hesitation. Monkeys delight in entertaining their friends and brightening the atmosphere in any way they can. To those of us who prefer quiet over noise, repose over activity, and consistently choose seriousness over silliness, the Monkey’s need to divert and amuse is downright annoying. But for Dragons, who adore celebration, invent reasons to host parties when none exist, and willingly participate in all general merrymaking, the Monkey’s antics provide a welcome relief from boredom. This year, you will have the opportunity to earn a significant amount of money. Nobody or nothing will stand in your way. The fearless Dragon protects and admires Monkeys. Take full advantage of this benevolence; and for once in your life, bask in the spotlight, seize that microphone, and confidently create a better life for yourself.` }
    }
};



    